            The data validation was successful. Now I'll proceed with the next step in the workflow - filtering the content. I'll use the data_processing_filter tool to process the data.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "options": {
    "filter_type": "basic",
    "criteria": {
      "include_all": true
    }
  }
}
</tool_call>

                        The filter operation timed out. I'll retry the operation with a shorter timeout setting to handle this error condition.

<tool_call>data_processing_filter
{
  "options": {
    "filter_type": "basic",
    "criteria": {
      "include_all": true
    },
    "timeout": 30
  }
}
</tool_call>

                        The filtering operation completed successfully after adjusting the timeout. Now I'll proceed with the final step in the workflow - transforming the data format. I'll use the data_processing_transformer tool to convert the data to JSON format (using the default output format as specified in the test environment rules).

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "json",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
